  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6520.38 sitting between the massive negative gamma wall at 6500 (-9.8B) and positive gamma cluster around 6530 (+4.9B), dealers are currently in a neutral hedging zone but biased toward selling any push higher given the PIN regime. The gex_surge event combined with spot trading below the 6566 flip point means dealers will aggressively sell rallies into the 6530-6535 resistance zone while providing strong support if price approaches the 6500 amplifying level where they'll be forced buyers. \n\nKey inflection points: Watch for dealer selling pressure to intensify above 6530, while any break toward 6500 should trigger aggressive dealer buying as they hedge short gamma exposure.",
